1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,211
Just as I was about to leave, in marched a delivery man with a gift of liquid refreshment from a local tire-recapping firm.

2
00:00:08,560 --> 00:00:13,570
My friend was obviously provoked, and with a certain amount of chill in his voice,

3
00:00:13,760 --> 00:00:17,731
asked the delivery man to return the gift to its sender.

4
00:00:18,161 --> 00:00:22,851
After the delivery man left, my friend hastened to explain to me.

5
00:00:23,120 --> 00:00:24,851
Don't misunderstand.

6
00:00:24,961 --> 00:00:27,971
I like to give gifts, and I like to get them.

7
00:00:28,240 --> 00:00:33,810
Then he named a number of gifts he had already received from business friends that Christmas.

8
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:38,851
But, he went on, when the gift is just an attempt to get my business,

9
00:00:38,961 --> 00:00:41,250
an obvious bribe, I don't want it.

10
00:00:41,521 --> 00:00:47,251
I quit doing business with that firm three months ago, because their work isn't what it should be,

11
00:00:47,251 --> 00:00:49,251
and I don't like the employees.

12
00:00:49,361 --> 00:00:51,891
But their salesman keeps on calling.

13
00:00:52,401 --> 00:01:00,690
What burns me, he continued, is that last week that same blank salesman was in here and had the gall to say,

14
00:01:00,801 --> 00:01:03,251
I sure would like to get your business back.

15
00:01:03,361 --> 00:01:06,850
I'm going to tell Santa to be real good to you this year.

16
00:01:07,121 --> 00:01:13,411
If I hadn't sent their booze back, the first thing that so and so would have said to me next time he's in is,

17
00:01:13,441 --> 00:01:16,450
I'll bet you enjoyed our gift, didn't you?

18
00:01:16,961 --> 00:01:22,210
Friendship can't be bought, and when we try, we lose in two ways.

19
00:01:22,401 --> 00:01:24,210
One, we waste money.

20
00:01:24,401 --> 00:01:26,930
Two, we create contempt.

21
00:01:28,001 --> 00:01:30,690
Take the initiative in building friendships.

22
00:01:30,881 --> 00:01:32,690
Leaders always do.

23
00:01:33,041 --> 00:01:37,970
It's easy and natural for us to tell ourselves, let him make the first move.

24
00:01:38,081 --> 00:01:39,491
Let them call us.

25
00:01:39,681 --> 00:01:41,491
Let her speak first.

26
00:01:41,761 --> 00:01:45,570
It's easy too, virtually, to ignore other people.

27
00:01:46,081 --> 00:01:51,011
Yes, it's easy and natural, but it isn't right thinking toward people.

28
00:01:51,281 --> 00:01:55,970
If you follow the rule of letting the other person build the foundation for friendship,

29
00:01:56,081 --> 00:01:58,051
you may not have many friends.

30
00:01:58,561 --> 00:02:03,570
Actually, it's a mark of real leadership to take the lead in getting to know people.

31
00:02:03,761 --> 00:02:08,371
Next time you are in a large group, observe something very significant.

